variance_explanation:
The variance is mainly attributable to new in-year funding received through Supplementary Estimates and Treasury Board Central Votes to:
-	Support the partial visa imposition on Mexico and ensure that the department is able to establish a high level of client service for all applicants from Mexico;
-	Carry forward eligible lapsing funds from 2023-24 to 2024-25;
-	Support overseas network positions changes and other cost adjustments requiring a transfer from Global Affairs Canada;
-	Reimburse eligible paylist expenditures; and
-	Deliver an improved cross-channel experience for IRCC clients as part of the Digital Platform Modernization Initiative Tranche 1.

The variance is also attributable to an increase in statutory authorities following adjustments made to align with actual expenditures, including adjustments to the Employee Benefits Plan and other special statutory items; and an internal reallocation of funds following a departmental reorganization.

The variance is mainly attributable to new in-year funding received through Supplementary Estimates and Treasury Board Central Votes to:
-	Support asylum seekers in Quebec by providing a one-time grant payment to cover housing-related pressures associated with heightened volumes of asylum claimants;
-	Compensate provinces and municipalities for the interim housing of asylum claimants through the Interim Housing Assistance Program;
-	Cover incremental costs related to the provision of health-care benefits to eligible beneficiaries as part of the Interim Federal Health Program;
-	Continue providing temporary accommodations to asylum claimants who do not have access to shelters or affordable housing; and
-	Carry forward eligible lapsing funds from 2023-24 to 2024-25.

The variance is mainly attributable to new in-year funding received through Supplementary Estimates and Treasury Board Central Votes to:
-	Deliver an improved cross-channel experience for IRCC clients as part of the Digital Platform Modernization Initiative Tranche 1;
-	Procure a new back-end Case Management Platform as part of the Digital Platform Modernization Initiative Tranche 2; 
-	Carry forward eligible lapsing funds from 2023-24 to 2024-25; and
-	Reimburse eligible paylist expenditures.

The variance is also attributable to an increase in statutory authorities following adjustments made to align with actual expenditures, including adjustments to the Employee Benefit Plan; and an internal reallocation of funds from other lapsing programs in order to meet operational priorities.

